items.title: Citigroup swings to fourth-quarter profit, tops estimates on investment banking strength
items.description: The fourth-quarter report comes after a year where Citi's stock rose almost 37%, outperforming the S&P 500.

items.title: Goldman backs up our bank stock shuffle with strong earnings, upbeat M&A outlook
items.description: Shares popped roughly 6% to more than $600 apiece after a fourth-quarter revenue and earnings beat.

items.title: Wells Fargo shares surge post-earnings as Wall Street wisely focuses on the big picture
items.description: While the reported numbers were solid, an upbeat outlook for 2025 stole the show.

items.title: BlackRock delivers earnings beat that proves recent sellers of the stock wrong
items.description: New deals will help BlackRock obtain "higher and more durable organic growth," CEO Larry Fink said on the post-earnings call with investors.
